                <note rend="inline" type="source">842.612 Peaches/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Ottawa</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-08T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your despatch No. 22, July 18, 1927, stated Motherwell promised decision
                    respecting peach embargo by July 21. Please telegraph status of this matter.
                    Peach interests are pressing for action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
